gitCommit.subject: test(e2e): improve sidebar node expansion reliability and update assets
gitCommit.body:
test(e2e): improve sidebar node expansion reliability and update assets

* Replace the bundled JS asset – removed `index-CEhqCZAe.js`, added `index-BMixMliY.js` – and update all references in `backend/frontend/dist/index.html` and the service‑worker precache manifest.
* Add a `data-testid="expand‑icon-<node.id>"` attribute to the expand icon in `frontend/src/components/SidebarNode.tsx` for stable targeting.
* Extend `e2e/AGENTS.md` with best‑practice guidance: use explicit `data-testid`s, click visible portions of overlays, and verify interactive elements meet a minimum 16 × 16 px clickable area.
* Refactor `e2e/page-crud.spec.ts` and `e2e/page-hierarchy.spec.ts` to locate the expand icon via the new testid, assert its visibility and size, and click it directly rather than relying on fragile positional selectors.
* Clean up the obsolete asset file and its entry in the service‑worker precache list.
